Configuration properties for a web driver.

The WebDriverConfig class is annotated with @Component and @ConfigurationProperties(prefix = "web-driver") to indicate that it serves as a configuration bean for web driver-related properties. Instances of this class are used to configure various aspects of the web driver, such as the executable path, user agent, page load timeout, and implicit wait time.

The webDriverExecutable property represents the path to the web driver executable. The userAgent property specifies the user agent string to be used by the web driver. The pageLoadTimeout property indicates the maximum time to wait for a page to load. The implicitlyWait property defines the maximum time to wait for an element to be found when performing an implicit wait.

Configuring web driver properties through this class allows for customization and fine-tuning of web driver behavior within an application.
